data.title: Eurovision 2024 Tonight: National final in Georgia
data.meta_description: Eurovision 2024 news: Tonight, the Georgian national final for the Eurovision Song Contest 2010 will be held. Out of six songs, it will be decided which one will be performed
data.meta_site_name: Eurovision News, Polls and Information by ESCToday
data.text:
Tonight, the Georgian national final for the Eurovision Song Contest 2010 will be held. Out of six songs, it will be decided which one will be performed by Sopho Nizharadze in Oslo.

The show

The show to be broadcast on Channel 1 will start at 17:30 CET (20:30 local time). Sopho Nizharadze will perform all six songs the winning entry will be chosen from.

How to watch?

A webcast will be made available here andon eurovision.tv here (requires Octoshape plugin).

Entries

Running order with composer/lyricist in brackets.

Our world

(Mikheil Mdinaradze)

Sing my song

(Svika Pick)

Never give in

(Tinatin Japaridze, Ben Robbins, Billy Livsey)

For eternity

(Andrej BabiÄ�/Carlos Coelho)

Call me

(Brandon Stone)

Shine

(Hanne Sørvaag, Harry Sommerdahl, Christian Leuzzi)

Your opinion

You can vote for your favourite song in our poll here.

As Georgia withdrew from the Eurovision Song Contest 2009, the country's last entry in the contest was Peace will come in 2008. Performed by Diana Gurtskaya, it finished fifth in the second semi final and eleventh in the final. In 2010, the country will compete in the second semi final of the Eurovision Song Contest on 27th May.
